-- Dow Chemical, Aksa to Sign Agreement on Investment, Agency Says
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2011-12-19T08:40:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/dow-chemical-aksa-to-sign-agreement-on-investment-agency-says.html
Dow Chemical Co. (DOW) , the largest U.S.
chemicals manufacturer, and  Aksa Akrilik Kimya Sanayii AS (AKSA)  will
sign an agreement in Istanbul tomorrow for a petrochemical
investment,  Turkey ’s investment promotion agency said.  Akkok Group Chief Executive Mehmet Ali Berkman and Dow
Chemical Company Executive Vice President Heinz Haller will be
present at tomorrow’s ceremony, the agency said in an e-mailed
statement today. Akkok is the parent company of Aksa Akrilik
Kimya Sanayii AS, the Turkish producer of synthetic fibers.  Akkok is planning a 50-50 joint venture with Dow Chemical
Co. for production in Turkey, Berkman said in an interview on
Oct 6.  Aksa shares jumped 5.2 percent to 4.5 liras at 10:33 a.m.
today in Istanbul, their biggest increase since Sept. 27.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
